{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]I'm writing this answer to the [F]Galveston [C]Rose
[D7]The answer to a sad broken [G7]heart
[C]My whole world it crumbled when I [F]read your last [C]note
[G7]Saying that we forever must [C]part
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[F]Oh I realize now you were innocent [C]dear
[D7]When in anger I said we were [G7]through
[C]For as all the long years have [F]passed slowly [C]away
[G7]I find that I'll always love [C]you
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]There were tears on your cheeks when I bid you [C]goodbye
[D7]And you pleaded with me not to [G7]go
[C]These last years I have paid for the [F]wrong I have [C]done
[G7]To my sweetheart the Galveston [C]Rose
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[F]Now they say you are resting in a lonely [C]churchyard
[D7]Where the violets and red roses [G7]hide
[C]And I pray when I die my [F]request they will [C]fill
[G7]And lay me to rest by your [C]side
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[F]I have longed and I've yearned for you many a [C]time
[D7]And wished I could undo the [G7]past
[C]And hold you again in my [F]arms [C]tenderly
[G7]And live with you dear to the [C]last
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
[F]Now you've heard my sad answer to a flower so [C]fair
[D7]One I loved more than anyone [G7]knows
[C]With God's help I'll repay for the [F]sorrow and [C]tears
[G7]That I brought to my Galveston [C]Rose
{end_of_verse}
